ai_Badger.description: A MIB module for AI's AIBadger

aibadgerSAMVer.name: aibadgerSAMVer
aibadgerSAMVer.description: The aibadgerSAMVer is its hardware and software version for the aibadger and the SAM board.

aibadgerMACAddr.name: aibadgerMACAddr
aibadgerMACAddr.description: The aibadgerMACAddr is the MAC Address of the SAM board.

aibadgerStatus.name: aibadgerStatus
aibadgerStatus.description: The aibadgerStatus is the status of the aibadger. The possible values are: working, failed, disabled.

aibadgerTimeTag.name: aibadgerTimeTag
aibadgerTimeTag.description: The aibadgerTimeTag is the time stamp when the aibadger status changed.

aibadgerRsp.name: aibadgerRsp
aibadgerRsp.description: The aibadgerRsp is the descriptive string for the aibadger status.

aibadgerTrapAck.name: aibadgerTrapAck
aibadgerTrapAck.description: The aibadgerTrapAck contains trap ID related information if the trap needs to be acknowledged by the manager.

aibadgerTest.name: aibadgerTest
aibadgerTest.description: The aibadgerTest is for testing the SNMP get and set command for SNMP. Whenever this string is changed it will send a trap to the SNMP manager

deviceTbl.name: deviceTbl
deviceTbl.description: The (conceptual) table listing the network element devices connected to the SAM board

deviceTblEntry.name: deviceTblEntry
deviceTblEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the deviceTbl.

devTblIndex.name: devTblIndex
devTblIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used for identifying instances of the columnar objects in the deviceTbl.

devName.name: devName
devName.description: The devName is the name of the BAM or other device in the device table.

devMacAddr.name: devMacAddr
devMacAddr.description: The devMacAddr is the Mac Address or hardware board related address for the device in the device table.

devVersion.name: devVersion
devVersion.description: The devVersion is the hardware and software version for the device in the device table.

devBiCnt.name: devBiCnt
devBiCnt.description: The devBiCnt is the number of bistate points for the device in the device table.

devAnaCnt.name: devAnaCnt
devAnaCnt.description: The devAnaCnt is the number of analog points for the device in the device table.

devCtrlCnt.name: devCtrlCnt
devCtrlCnt.description: The devCtrlCnt is the number of control points for the device in the device table.

devStatus.name: devStatus
devStatus.description: The devStatus is current Status for the device in the device table. The possiable values are: working,failed, disabled.

devStatusTimeTag.name: devStatusTimeTag
devStatusTimeTag.description: The devStatusTimeTag is time stamp of the current status for the device in the device table.

devRspStr.name: devRspStr
devRspStr.description: The devRspStr is more descriptive string for the current status about this device.

devTrapAck.name: devTrapAck
devTrapAck.description: The devTrapAck contains trap ID related information if the trap needs to be acknowledged by the manager.

bistateTblEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the deviceTbl.

biAlmID.description: The biAlmID is the unique alarm identifier for the aibadger.

biNumber.description: The biNumber is the physical number for the bistatepoint.

biName.description: The biName is the user assigned name for this bistate point.

biStatus.description: The biStatus is the current status for this bistate point. The possiable values are: critical, major, minor-b, minor-a, normal, informational, not-defined, maintenance.

biRspStr.description: The biRspStr is the descriptive string for this current status for this bistate point.

biStatusTimeTag.description: The biStatusTimeTag is the time stamp for the current status when the status changed for this bistate point.

biTrapAck.name: biTrapAck
biTrapAck.description: The biTrapAck contains trap IP related information if the trap needs to be acknowledged by the manager.

ctrlTblIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used for identifying instances of the columnar objects in the ctrlstateTbl.

ctrlAlmID.description: The ctrlAlmID is the unique alarm identifier for the aibadger.

ctrlNumber.name: ctrlNumber
ctrlNumber.description: The ctrlNumber is the physical number for the control point.

ctrlName.description: The ctrlName is the user assigned name for this control point.

ctrlStatus.description: The ctrlStatus is the current status for this control point. The possiable values are: critical, major, minor-b, minor-a, normal, informational, not-defined, maintenance.

ctrlState.description: The ctrlState represents the current state of the control point.1--latch off,2--latch on,3--momentary off,4--momentary on.

snmpManagerTbl.name: snmpManagerTbl
snmpManagerTbl.description: The (conceptual) table listing all of SNMP manager's names,IP addresses and community names configured on the aibadger

snmpManagerTblEntry.name: snmpManagerTblEntry
snmpManagerTblEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the snmp manager table.

snmpTblIndex.name: snmpTblIndex
snmpTblIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used for identifying instances of the columnar objects in the snmpManagerTbl.

name.name: name
name.description: The name is the name string for the SNMP manager.

ipAddr.name: ipAddr
ipAddr.description: The ipAddr is the IP address for the SNMP manager.

community.name: community
community.description: The commnity is the community name string for the SNMP manager.

trapVer.name: trapVer
trapVer.description: The trapVer is the SNMP trap version the aibadger is configured to send. The possiable values are v1, v2.

trapControl.name: trapControl
trapControl.description: The trapControl indicates the aibadger is configured to enable or disable all traps. The possiable values are enable or disable.

trapSerControl.name: trapSerControl
trapSerControl.description: The trapSerControl is the severity threshold that triggers a trap if trap control is enabled on the aibadger. The possiable severity values are: critical,major,minor-a,minor-b

ackControl.name: ackControl
ackControl.description: The ackControl indicates if the aibadger is configured to expect an acknowlegement from an SNMP manager when it sends a trap. The SNMP manager must support this feature if you enable ackControl on the aibadger. The possiable values for ackControl are enable or disable.

ackSerControl.name: ackSerControl
ackSerControl.description: The ackSerControl is the trap severity threshold that enables an acknowlegement from a SNMP manager if the ackControl is enabled on the aibadger. The SNMP manager must support this feature. The possiable severity values are: critical, major,minor-a,minor-b

healthCheck.name: healthCheck
healthCheck.description: The SNMP trap is generated every 24 hours to indicate that the SAM board is still there.

maintenaceBistateTrap.description: The SNMP trap is generated when a bistate point has change of state and it is currently in maintenance state.
